where exactly are the ovaries i have some pain off to one side it is not the appendix side but my left hand side if i were to put two fingers under my bellybutton and go straight across to the left that is where it is it doesn't hurt all the time but occasionally i feel like a cramping there is this where my ovary would be i thought they were a lot lower anyway i am a little concerned about ectopic pregnancy but i am not having any real severe pain i will be six weeks on monday any ideas i am hoping just growing pains or something i had the same question for so long in the anatomical drawings they show you the uterus and ovaries but not where they are on you to scale if you go to the horizontal line where your belly starts to round and then meet that vertically from the edge of your natural bikini line edge on either side that's where your ovaries are still you may still feel them higher up if there's a problem i have an enlarged ovary on my left side that goes up several inches i wasn't really aware of it until i was about weeks and it decided to hurt really really badly and i ended up in the hospital so please have your doctor do an ultrasound as soon as you can get in to find out what it is and make sure it's under control good luck Ectopic pregnancy Miscarriage Obstetrics Abdomen Stomach cancer Polycystic ovary syndrome Menstrual cycle Androgen insensitivity syndrome Pregnancy Breastfeeding EastEnders Prostate cancer Ovary Uterus Puberty Abortion Gynaecology Diving Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Drill bit Childbirth Aerial (dance move) Ovarian cancer Cryptorchidism Sexual reproduction Breech birth Gonorrhoea Equine conformation Professional wrestling holds In vitro fertilisation Intersex surgery Social rule Theory of conduct Urinary incontinence Pitaten Knife Premature birth Milton H. Erickson Piccolo Junior Saga Violin Endometrial cancer About a Boy Colorectal cancer Radiation therapy Professional wrestling throws The Contender (television series) Anatomical terms of l